(1x)"},"H2908":{"id":"H2908","lemma":"טְוָת","translit":"ṭᵉvâth","pron":"tev-awth'","derivation":"(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to H2901 (טָוָה);","strongs_def":"hunger (as twisting)","kjv_def":"fasting.","pos":"adverb","usage":"fasting(1x)"},"H2909":{"id":"H2909","lemma":"טָחָה","translit":"ṭâchâh","pron":"taw-khaw'","derivation":"a primitive root;","strongs_def":"to stretch a bow, as an archer","kjv_def":"(bow-) shot.","pos":"verb"},"H2910":{"id":"H2910","lemma":"טֻחָה","translit":"ṭuchâh","pron":"too-khaw'","derivation":"from H2909 (טָחָה) (or H2902 (טוּחַ)) in the sense of overlaying;","strongs_def":"(in the plural only) the kidneys (as being covered); hence (figuratively) the inmost thought","kjv_def":"inward parts.","pos":"feminine noun"},"H2911":{"id":"H2911","lemma":"טְחוֹן","translit":"ṭᵉchôwn","pron":"tekh-one'","derivation":"from H2912 (טָחַן);","strongs_def":"a hand mill; hence, a millstone","kjv_def":"to grind.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"grind(1x)"},"H2912":{"id":"H2912","lemma":"טָחַן","translit":"ṭâchan","pron":"taw-khan'","derivation":"a primitive root;","strongs_def":"to grind meal; hence, to be aconcubine (that being their employment)","kjv_def":"grind(-er).","pos":"verb","usage":"grind(7x), grinder(1x)"},"H2913":{"id":"H2913","lemma":"טַחֲנָה","translit":"ṭachănâh","pron":"takh-an-aw'","derivation":"from H2912 (טָחַן);","strongs_def":"a hand mill; hence (figuratively) chewing","kjv_def":"grinding.","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"grinding(1x)"},"H2914":{"id":"H2914","lemma":"טְחֹר","translit":"ṭᵉchôr","pron":"tekh-ore'","derivation":"from an unused root meaning to burn;","strongs_def":"a boil or ulcer (from the inflammation), especially a tumorin the anus or pudenda (the piles)","kjv_def":"emerod.","pos":"masculine plural noun","usage":"emerods(8x)"},"H2915":{"id":"H2915","lemma":"טִיחַ","translit":"ṭîyach","pron":"tee'akh","derivation":"from (the equiv. of) H2902 (טוּחַ);","strongs_def":"mortar or plaster","kjv_def":"daubing.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"daubing(1x)"},"H2916":{"id":"H2916","lemma":"טִיט","translit":"ṭîyṭ","pron":"teet","derivation":"from an unused root meaning apparently to be sticky (rather perb. a demonstrative); from H2894 (טוּא), through the idea of dirt to be swept away);","strongs_def":"mud or clay; figuratively, calamity","kjv_def":"clay, dirt, mire.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"mire(8x), clay(3x), dirt(2x)"},"H2917":{"id":"H2917","lemma":"טִין","translit":"ṭîyn","pron":"teen","derivation":"(Aramaic) perhaps, by interchange, for a word corresponding to H2916 (טִיט);","strongs_def":"clay","kjv_def":"miry.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"miry(2x)"},"H2918":{"id":"H2918","lemma":"טִירָה","translit":"ṭîyrâh","pron":"tee-raw'","derivation":"feminine of (an equivalent to) H2905 (טוּר);","strongs_def":"a wall; hence, a fortress or a hamlet","kjv_def":"(goodly) castle, habitation, palace, row.","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"castle(3x), palace(2x), row(1x), habitation(1x)"},"H2919":{"id":"H2919","lemma":"טַל","translit":"ṭal","pron":"tal","derivation":"from H2926 (טָלַל);","strongs_def":"dew (as covering vegetation)","kjv_def":"dew.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"dew(31x)"},"H2920":{"id":"H2920","lemma":"טַל","translit":"ṭal","pron":"tal","derivation":"(Aramaic) the same as H2919 (טַל)","strongs_def":"{dew (as covering vegetation)}","kjv_def":"dew.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"dew(5x)"},"H2921":{"id":"H2921","lemma":"טָלָא","translit":"ṭâlâʼ","pron":"taw-law'","derivation":"a primitive root;","strongs_def":"properly, to cover with pieces; i.e. (by implication) to spot or variegate (as tapestry)","kjv_def":"clouted, with divers colours, spotted.","pos":"verb","usage":"spotted(6x), clouted(1x)"},"H2922":{"id":"H2922","lemma":"טְלָא","translit":"ṭᵉlâʼ","pron":"tel-aw'","derivation":"apparently from H2921 (טָלָא) in the (orig.) sense of covering (for protection); (compare H2924 (טָלֶה))","strongs_def":"a lamb","kjv_def":"lamb.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"lamb(1x)"},"H2923":{"id":"H2923","lemma":"טְלָאִים","translit":"Ṭᵉlâʼîym","pron":"tel-aw-eem'","derivation":"from the plural of H2922 (טְלָא); lambs;","strongs_def":"Telaim, a place in Palestine","kjv_def":"Telaim."},"H2924":{"id":"H2924","lemma":"טָלֶה","translit":"ṭâleh","pron":"taw-leh'","derivation":"by variation for H2922 (טְלָא);","strongs_def":"a lamb","kjv_def":"lamb.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"lamb(2x)"},"H2925":{"id":"H2925","lemma":"טַלְטֵלָה","translit":"ṭalṭêlâh","pron":"tal-tay-law'","derivation":"from H2904 (טוּל);","strongs_def":"overthrow or rejection","kjv_def":"captivity.","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"captivity(1x)"},"H2926":{"id":"H2926","lemma":"טָלַל","translit":"ṭâlal","pron":"taw-lal'","derivation":"a primitive root;","strongs_def":"properly, to strew over, i.e. (by implication) to cover in or plate (with beams)","kjv_def":"cover.","pos":"verb","usage":"cover(1x)"},"H2927":{"id":"H2927","lemma":"טְלַל","translit":"ṭᵉlal","pron":"tel-al'","derivation":"(Aramaic) corresponding to H2926 (טָלַל);","strongs_def":"to cover with shade","kjv_def":"have a shadow.","pos":"verb","usage":"shadow(1x)"},"H2928":{"id":"H2928","lemma":"טֶלֶם","translit":"Ṭelem","pron":"teh'-lem","derivation":"from an unused root meaning to break up or treat violently; oppression;","strongs_def":"Telem, the name of a place in Idumaea, also of a temple doorkeeper","kjv_def":"Telem.","pos":"proper locative noun, proper masculine noun","usage":"Telem(2x)"},"H2929":{"id":"H2929","lemma":"טַלְמוֹן","translit":"Ṭalmôwn","pron":"tal-mone'","derivation":"from the same as H2728 (חָרְגֹּל); oppressive;","strongs_def":"Talmon, a temple doorkeeper","kjv_def":"Talmon.","pos":"proper masculine noun","usage":"Talmon(5x)"},"H2930":{"id":"H2930","lemma":"טָמֵא","translit":"ṭâmêʼ","pron":"taw-may'","derivation":"a primitive root;","strongs_def":"to be foul, especially in a ceremial or moral sense (contaminated)","kjv_def":"defile (self), pollute (self), be (make, make self, pronounce) unclean, [idiom] utterly.","pos":"verb","usage":"unclean(74x), defile(71x), pollute(14x), uncleanness(1x), utterly(1x)"},"H2931":{"id":"H2931","lemma":"טָמֵא","translit":"ṭâmêʼ","pron":"taw-may'","derivation":"from H2930 (טָמֵא);","strongs_def":"foul in a religious sense","kjv_def":"defiled, [phrase] infamous, polluted(-tion), unclean.","pos":"adjective","usage":"unclean(79x), defiled(5x), infamous(1x), polluted(1x), pollution(1x)"},"H2932":{"id":"H2932","lemma":"טֻמְאָה","translit":"ṭumʼâh","pron":"toom-aw'","derivation":"from H2930 (טָמֵא);","strongs_def":"religious impurity","kjv_def":"filthiness, unclean(-ness).","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"uncleanness(26x), filthiness(7x), unclean(4x)"},"H2933":{"id":"H2933","lemma":"טָמָה","translit":"ṭâmâh","pron":"taw-maw'","derivation":"a collateral form of H2930 (טָמֵא);","strongs_def":"to be impure in a religious sense","kjv_def":"be defiled, be reputed vile.","pos":"verb","usage":"defiled(1x), vile(1x)"},"H2934":{"id":"H2934","lemma":"טָמַן","translit":"ṭâman","pron":"taw-man'","derivation":"a primitive root;","strongs_def":"to hide (by covering over)","kjv_def":"hide, lay privily, in secret.","pos":"verb","usage":"hide(26x), laid(2x), secret(1x)"},"H2935":{"id":"H2935","lemma":"טֶנֶא","translit":"ṭeneʼ","pron":"teh'-neh","derivation":"from an unused root probably meaning to weave;","strongs_def":"a basket (of interlaced osiers)","kjv_def":"basket.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"basket(4x)"},"H2936":{"id":"H2936","lemma":"טָנַף","translit":"ṭânaph","pron":"taw-naf'","derivation":"a primitive root;","strongs_def":"to soil","kjv_def":"defile."},"H2937":{"id":"H2937","lemma":"טָעָה","translit":"ṭâʻâh","pron":"taw-aw'","derivation":"a primitive root;","strongs_def":"to wander; causatively to lead astray","kjv_def":"seduce.","pos":"verb","usage":"seduce(1x)"},"H2938":{"id":"H2938","lemma":"טָעַם","translit":"ṭâʻam","pron":"taw-am'","derivation":"a primitive root;","strongs_def":"to taste; figuratively, to perceive","kjv_def":"[idiom] but, perceive, taste.","pos":"verb","usage":"taste(10x), perceive(1x)"},"H2939":{"id":"H2939","lemma":"טְעַם","translit":"ṭᵉʻam","pron":"teh-am'","derivation":"(Aramaic) corresponding to H2938 (טָעַם);","strongs_def":"to taste; causatively to feed","kjv_def":"make to eat, feed.","pos":"verb","usage":"feed(1x)"},"H2940":{"id":"H2940","lemma":"טַעַם","translit":"ṭaʻam","pron":"tah'-am","derivation":"from H2938 (טָעַם);","strongs_def":"properly, a taste, i.e. (figuratively) perception; by implication, intelligence; transitively, a mandate","kjv_def":"advice, behaviour, decree, discretion, judgment, reason, taste, understanding.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"taste(5x), behaviour(2x), advice(1x), understanding(1x), judgment(1x), discretion(1x), reason(1x), decree(1x)"},"H2941":{"id":"H2941","lemma":"טַעַם","translit":"ṭaʻam","pron":"tah'-am","derivation":"(Aramaic) from H2939 (טְעַם); compare H2940 (טַעַם))","strongs_def":"properly, a taste, i.e.  ajudicial sentence","kjv_def":"account, [idiom] to be commanded, commandment, matter.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"commandment(2x), matter(1x), commanded(1x), accounts(1x)"},"H2942":{"id":"H2942","lemma":"טְעֵם","translit":"ṭᵉʻêm","pron":"teh-ame'","derivation":"(Aramaic) from H2939 (טְעַם), and equivalent to H2941 (טַעַם);","strongs_def":"properly, flavor; figuratively, judgment (both subjective and objective); hence, account (both subjectively and objectively)","kjv_def":"[phrase] chancellor, [phrase] command, commandment, decree, [phrase] regard, taste, wisdom.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"decree(13x), regarded(1x), commandment(2x), tasted(1x), wisdom(1x)"},"H2943":{"id":"H2943","lemma":"טָעַן","translit":"ṭâʻan","pron":"taw-an'","derivation":"a primitive root;","strongs_def":"to load a beast","kjv_def":"lade.","pos":"verb","usage":"lade(1x)"},"H2944":{"id":"H2944","lemma":"טָעַן","translit":"ṭâʻan","pron":"taw-an'","derivation":"a primitive root;","strongs_def":"to stab","kjv_def":"thrust through.","pos":"verb"},"H2945":{"id":"H2945","lemma":"טַף","translit":"ṭaph","pron":"taf","derivation":"from H2952 (טָפַף) (perhaps referring to the tripping gait of children);","strongs_def":"a family (mostly used collectively in the singular)","kjv_def":"(little) children (ones), families.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"children(12x), families(1x)"},"H2946":{"id":"H2946","lemma":"טָפַח","translit":"ṭâphach","pron":"taw-fakh'","derivation":"a primitive root; or perhaps a denominative from H2947 (טֵפַח), from dandling on the palms","strongs_def":"to flatten out or extend (as a tent); figuratively, to nurse achild (as promotive of growth);","kjv_def":"span, swaddle.","pos":"verb","usage":"span(1x), swaddle(1x)"},"H2947":{"id":"H2947","lemma":"טֵפַח","translit":"ṭêphach","pron":"tay'-fakh","derivation":"from H2946 (טָפַח);","strongs_def":"a spread of the hand, i.e. a palm-breadth (not 'span' of the fingers); architecturally, a corbel (as a supporting palm)","kjv_def":"coping, hand-breadth.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"coping(1x)"},"H2948":{"id":"H2948","lemma":"טֹפַח","translit":"ṭôphach","pron":"to'-fakh","derivation":"from H2946 (טָפַח) (the same as H2947 (טֵפַח))","strongs_def":"{a spread of the hand, i.e. a palm-breadth (not 'span' of the fingers); architecturally, a corbel (as a supporting palm)}","kjv_def":"hand-breadth (broad).","pos":"masculine noun"},"H2949":{"id":"H2949","lemma":"טִפֻּח","translit":"ṭippuch","pron":"tip-pookh'","derivation":"from H2946 (טָפַח);","strongs_def":"nursing","kjv_def":"span long.","pos":"masculine plural noun","usage":"span(1x)"},"H2950":{"id":"H2950","lemma":"טָפַל","translit":"ṭâphal","pron":"taw-fal'","derivation":"a primitive root;","strongs_def":"properly, to stick on as apatch; figuratively, to impute falsely","kjv_def":"forge(-r), sew up.","pos":"verb","usage":"forge(1x), forger(1x)"},"H2951":{"id":"H2951","lemma":"טִפְסַר","translit":"ṭiphçar","pron":"tif-sar'","derivation":"of foreign derivation;","strongs_def":"a military governor","